description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting full time opportunity has arisen for an experienced Children&#39;s nurse with excellent public health knowledge, to join our team of Children in Care Nurses at The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a diverse and interesting nursing role, working with children and young people between 0-19 years of age, carers and multiagency partners to drive forward the Local and National Agendas to improve the health outcomes of Looked after Children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have recent relevant experience of working with children and families within the community. You will possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills, be adept at prioritising and working flexibly and demonstrate knowledge of legislation and policy relating to Children in Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be an enthusiastic advocate for the children and have an excellent knowledge of safeguarding.&lt;/p&gt;
